Okay, I understand. I need to match order forms with invoices by selecting the corresponding checkboxes in the order and invoice tables, then click the "match" button, and finally click the "record" button.

```json
[
  {"click": "table:has-text(\"order\" i) >> tr >> input[type=checkbox]"},
  {"click": "table:has-text(\"invoice\" i) >> tr >> input[type=checkbox]"},
  {"click": "button:has-text(\"match\" i)"},
  {"click": "button:has-text(\"record\" i)"}
]
```
<OUTPUT_JSON>[{"click": "table:has-text(\"order\" i) >> tr >> input[type=checkbox]"}, {"click": "table:has-text(\"invoice\" i) >> tr >> input[type=checkbox]"}, {"click": "button:has-text(\"match\" i)"}, {"click": "button:has-text(\"record\" i)"}]</OUTPUT_JSON>
